# stack-audit suppression list — one grep -E regex per line, matched against the raw
# SEVERITY|DOMAIN|FINDING|FIX line. Blank lines and #-comments are ignored.
# Each block documents WHY the finding is known-acceptable. Keep patterns specific so
# they don't mask real regressions (e.g. match by image name, not namespace-wide).

# --- Third-party Helm/operator-managed images (observability) ---
# Set by upstream charts/operators (grafana, kiwigrid k8s-sidecar, otel-operator,
# victoria-metrics-operator), NOT our manifests. Chart VERSIONS are pinned in
# gitops/README.md; per-image @sha256 pinning would mean overriding chart values every
# release for low supply-chain gain. Our own apps/* images are digest-pinned per convention.
# anchored on the org boundary: matches '[<registry>/]grafana/grafana:' but NOT the
# 'notgrafana/grafana:' / 'myorg/notgrafana/grafana:' decoys the bare .* used to swallow.
image/pin.*image '([^'/]+/)?grafana/grafana:
image/pin.*kiwigrid/k8s-sidecar:
image/pin.*opentelemetry-collector-contrib:
image/pin.*open-telemetry/opentelemetry-operator/
image/pin.*victoriametrics/(victoria-logs|victoria-metrics|operator):

# --- Probe-less sidecars / collectors (no Service routes to them) ---
# kiwigrid k8s-sidecars (grafana sc-alerts/dashboard/datasources) and the otel
# collectors are not Service-backed, so a readinessProbe is moot.
workload/probe.*container grafana-sc-
workload/probe.*(node-collector|scrape-collector).*otc-container

# (zilean oversized-limit suppression REMOVED Jun 2026: check 01 now aggregates VM peak by
# WORKLOAD, so the prior pod's ~800Mi import burst is captured and the 2Gi limit reads as
# 2.5× peak — no longer a false positive. zilean's request was raised to 768Mi to match.)
